Cell.Data:
I. Crytek Online Privacy Policy: Introduction

Crytek GmbH and its subsidiary companies (Crytek) respect the privacy rights of consumers and recognize the importance of protecting the information collected about you. We have adopted this global Privacy Policy to explain how we store and use personal and non-personal information we collect online on our websites, during your use of our online products and/or services (including online game play) and on mobile platforms.

II. What Is Personal Information And When Does Crytek Collect It?

Crytek collects both personal and non-personal consumer information. Personal information collected by Crytek is discussed below in this section. Non-personal information is discussed below in Section III.

A. Personal Information Collected By Crytek

Personal information is information that identifies you and that may be used to contact you on-line or off-line. Crytek may collect personal information from our online visitors during:

• Gaming and other user behavior including gaming results;
• Warranty registration and requests;
• Customer support and/or technical service requests;
• Player match up and other head-to-head online competitions;
• Registration for games and/or special game-specific events;
• Newsletter subscriptions, referral services, and other marketing surveys and email campaigns;

• Registration for Crytek and/or other service accounts;
• Product, service and/or subscription orders;
• Service requests from third party service providers on our site; and
• Otherwise through use of our software, mobile or online services where personal information is required for use and/or participation.

